jZTEoPh8tlz10";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:600;s:6:"height";i:800;s:6:"source";s:123:"https://www.diychatroom.com/threads/chamberlain-garage-door-opener-3280-267-rapid-and-continuous-flashing-of-lights.523770/";s:6:"domain";s:19:"www.diychatroom.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:40:"garage door opener light flashes problem";s:4:"slug";s:40:"garage-door-opener-light-flashes-problem";s:5:"title";s:63:"Craftsman Garage Door Opener Troubleshooting Step By Step Guide";s:3:"alt";s:14:"garage adviser";s:3:"url";s:135:"https://garageadviser.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/diagnostic-led-up-down-arrow-craftsman.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:372x191/rscb3/ng:webp/ngcb3";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQMuord0yD2hoJcxPPkr4zJB9Igs79rTp5LVA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:191;s:6:"height";i:372;s:6:"source";s:71:"https://garageadviser.net/craftsman-garage-door-opener-troubleshooting/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"garageadviser.net";}}s:9:"sentences";a:55:{i:0;s:135:"Having your garage door light blink continuously is not only annoying its also a sign that there is something wrong with the mechanism.";i:1;s:68:"There are several reasons why your garage door opener is doing this.";i:2;s:119:"However the two most common reasons include a problem with the lock button and malfunctioning safety reversing sensors.";i:3;s:165:"If you own a new garage door opener that comes with a locking feature its possible someone may have accidentally locked your garage door by pressing the lock button.";i:4;s:150:"If you try to open your door using a remote while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door light will begin blinking continuously.";i:5;s:122:"Four flashes is the most common reason your opener lights may be flashing is because of your sensor eyes being misaligned.";i:6;s:125:"If an object has misaligned your sensor eyes then it breaks the electronic beam preventing the garage door to close properly.";i:7;s:44:"The door will stop and reverse back upwards.";i:8;s:96:"Garage Door Opener Blinking Light Sensor Fix Garage Tec Garage Door Repair Richardson - YouTube.";i:9;s:82:"Unplug the device for a second time and reconnect the control wiring to the motor.";i:10;s:59:"Locate the wall mounted controls and disconnect the wiring.";i:11;s:74:"Use your garage door opener remote to test the functionality of your door.";i:12;s:49:"What does it mean when your garage light flashes.";i:13;s:84:"One flash indicates that your safety sensor wire may be open broken or disconnected.";i:14;s:39:"If your opener flashes twice then your.";i:15;s:63:"Garage Door Opener Lights Flash and the Garage Door Wont Close.";i:16;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:17;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:18;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:19;s:137:"If your garage door sending sensor is showing a yellow light and the other does not show a green light -it is likely they are misaligned.";i:20;s:49:"You may want to check the back of the motor unit.";i:21;s:71:"The back of the motor has a circuit board with a service light as well.";i:22;s:85:"The blink rate on the garage door opener service light points to various error codes.";i:23;s:57:"Craftsman Garage Door Opener Light Blinking Continuously.";i:24;s:123:"I attempted to open my Craftsman belt-drive opener model 13953914D yesterday afternoon with the remote and it wouldnt open.";i:25;s:91:"I entered the garage and the light bulbs in the unit were flashing on and off continuously.";i:26;s:69:"I unplugged the unit and plugged it back in to see if it would reset.";i:27;s:103:"Did you know that the type of bulb in your garage door opener can prevent it from functioning properly.";i:28;s:30:"Watch the video to learn more.";i:29;s:110:"This message is an indication that the battery in the door sensor is low and the battery needs to be replaced.";i:30;s:83:"After replacing the battery in your door sensor it can take up to 6 openings and c.";i:31;s:90:"Troubleshooting Guide for Connecting Your myQ Smart Garage Control to the myQ Door Sensor.";i:32;s:259:"Troubleshooting a LiftMaster opener with a flashing light involves inspection of the safety-reverse sensing systemLiftMaster motors will not operate when something obstructs the infrared beam between the safety sensors at the bottom of the garage door tracks.";i:33;s:56:"The main light will blink 10 times indicating a problem.";i:34;s:139:"If your garage door opener wont open and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:35;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:36;s:119:"Press and hold the button on the remote until the light bulb on the opener blinks indicating the opener has been reset.";i:37;s:66:"Also What does it mean when my garage door light flashes 10 times.";i:38;s:90:"Ten flashes of the light tells you there is a problem with the door safety sensor circuit.";i:39;s:30:"Look at the leds on both door.";i:40;s:191:"For example the Craftsman garage door opener troubleshooting for the light flashing 5 times may involve motor replacement if the door travels smoothly and the code appears after a single use.";i:41;s:187:"Once you figure out which part is causing the error code search for your model number to find a complete list of replacement parts for your garage door opener and order the part you need.";i:42;s:172:"When your Craftsman garage door opener is overheating or hums and doesnt move its a sign that there is a problem with the garage doors mechanism or the motor is overheated.";i:43;s:188:"This problem is confirmed with the Diagnostic LED flashing five times or with the error code 1-5 on newer devices which means the UP arrow blinks once and the DOWN arrow blinks five times.";i:44;s:130:"There are some instances when your new Chamberlain garage door opener lights keep flashing but the garage door wont close or open.";i:45;s:73:"The problem could lie in the LOCK button or the safety reversing sensors.";i:46;s:63:"Someone must have turned on the LOCK feature on the motor unit.";i:47;s:132:"When you try to access your door using a remote or clicker while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door light.";i:48;s:30:"Opener light does not turn on.";i:49;s:47:"- Replace the light bulbsmaximum 60 watts each.";i:50;s:79:"Use a garage door opener light bulb if regular type bulb burns out prematurely.";i:51;s:31:"Opener light does not turn off.";i:52;s:39:"- Is the wall control Light Feature on.";i:53;s:31:"Press Light Button to turn off.";i:54;s:34:"Applies only to Elite 2007 models.";}}